---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Soul"
  description="A bit about us."
  enableClientRouter={true}
>
  <section class="about-shell layout-shell page-shell">
    <div class="about-grid layout-grid">
      <article class="about">

        <h1 class="about-title">Soul.</h1>

        <p class="p--intro">
          We're a small studio outside Stockholm that builds websites, apps, and digital things for people and companies who'd rather not blend in. The internet is full of work that could belong to anyone. We make the kind that could only belong to you.
        </p>

        <p class="p--punch">
          We're<br>chasing soul.
        </p>

        <p class="p--body p--tilt-left">
          That's the real job, as we see it. Not just something that looks good or loads fast, but something that feels like the actual person or company behind it. Most sites are a costume. We're trying to build the opposite: the thing underneath, made visible.
        </p>

        <p class="p--body p--right">
          A site should sound like <em>you talking</em>, not like a template wearing your logo.
        </p>

        <p class="p--display">
          grounded,<br>not<br>generic.
        </p>

        <p class="p--body p--tilt-right">
          So we spend more time than we probably should figuring out who you actually are: how you talk, what you care about, what makes you different from the ten others doing the same thing. Then we build outward from that. Every typeface, colour, margin and line is a decision, and we make them in service of that one truth instead of decorating around it.
        </p>

        <p class="p--punch p--center">
          We say no<br>a lot.
        </p>

        <p class="p--body">
          That part's true to the name. Features nobody asked for, pages that fill space, the shiny stuff that exists so a deck felt expensive. We'll usually try to talk you out of it. Not to be difficult. Because every thing that doesn't belong quietly drowns out the things that do. Less in the way means more of you comes through.
        </p>

        <p class="p--body p--tilt-left">
          We'd rather build one honest thing that actually sounds like you than ten clever things that sound like a committee. Smaller, sharper, unmistakably yours.
        </p>

        <p class="p--outro">
          Nope to the noise.<br>Nope to the template.<br>Yes to the <strong>soul underneath it all</strong>.
        </p>

      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
  }

  .about {
    grid-column: 3 / 11;
    /* Top spacing comes from .page-shell (--space-section), matching the
       work page; keep the generous bottom padding only. */
    padding-block: 0 clamp(6rem, 14vw, 12rem);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    overflow-x: hidden;
    transition: background 0.3s ease, color 0.3s ease;
  }

  .about p {
    font-family: var(--font-family-prose);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Big display title, matching the work page's intro display. */
  .about-title {
    font-family: var(--font-family-base);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 9vw, 8rem);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-black);
    line-height: 0.9;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 clamp(3rem, 8vw, 7rem);
    color: var(--brand-purple);
  }

  :global([data-theme="experimental"]) .about-title {
    color: var(--neutral-50);
  }

  .about .p--intro {
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin-bottom: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem);
  }

  .about .p--punch {
    font-family: var(--font-family-base);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    max-width: 18ch;
    margin-bottom: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem);
  }

  .about .p--body {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.8vw, 1.25rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 48ch;
    margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);
  }

  .about .p--right {
    margin-inline-start: auto;
    text-align: right;
  }

  .about .p--display {
    font-family: var(--font-family-base);
    font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 12vw, 10rem);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-black);
    line-height: 0.9;
    letter-spacing: -0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-block: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem);
  }

  .about .p--center {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 100%;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .about .p--outro {
    font-family: var(--font-family-base);
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    line-height: 1.35;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-top: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem);
  }

  .about .p--tilt-left {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.8vw, 1.25rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 44ch;
    transform: rotate(-1.5deg);
    margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);
  }

  .about .p--tilt-right {
    transform: rotate(1deg);
  }

  /* Experimental theme */
  :global([data-theme="experimental"]) .about {
    color: var(--brand-green);
  }

  :global([data-theme="experimental"]) .about p {
    color: var(--brand-green);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about {
      grid-column: 1 / -1;
    }
  }
</style>
